      • getId

        public java.lang.String getId()
        The generated unique id of the Certification. There might no longer be an object with this id in the database, in which case you must look for an CertificationArchive with a sourceId property of the same value.

      • setId

        public void setId(java.lang.String s)

      • getType

        public Certification.Type getType()
        The type of the certification. Typically the certification list will be filtered so that it only contains the most recent certification of a given type.

        We could get this indirectly from certification, but keeping it locally allows for filtering of the list without having to fetch an CertificationArchive. Same for completed and certifier.

      • getIdentitySnapshotId

        public java.lang.String getIdentitySnapshotId()
        Return the ID of the IdentitySnapshot that holds the state of the identity at the time that the certification was created. This might be null for non-identity certifications or for CertificationLinks that were created before this property was added (in 6.0).
